________________________________________
Safe Work Methods and Solutions
Topic 1: Taint Analysis
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Static and Dynamic Analysis Tools
‚Ä¢	Solution: Utilize static and dynamic analysis tools that offer taint analysis features. These tools can automatically trace the flow of tainted data across the codebase.
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Code Annotations
‚Ä¢	Solution: Use code annotations to mark trusted and untrusted data sources. This makes it easier to perform manual taint analysis during code reviews.
Topic 2: Cloud Secrets Detection
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Secrets Management Systems
‚Ä¢	Solution: Use a centralized secrets management system like AWS Secrets Manager or HashiCorp Vault to store, manage, and retrieve secrets securely.
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Environment Variables
‚Ä¢	Solution: Store secrets in environment variables instead of hardcoding them into the application. This adds an extra layer of security and makes it easier to manage secrets.
Topic 3: Buffer Overflows
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Bounds Checking
‚Ä¢	Solution: Always perform bounds checking before writing data to a buffer. This can prevent buffer overflows by ensuring that the data fits within the allocated buffer.
‚Ä¢	Safe Work Method: Safe Libraries
‚Ä¢	Solution: Use libraries that are designed to handle buffer operations securely. For example, in C/C++, prefer using functions like strncpy() over strcpy().
‚Ä¢	________________________________________
