Day 4: OWASP Top 10 - From Understanding to Mastery
Overview
Day 4 will focus on a deep dive into selected OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities, using Bloom's Taxonomy to guide the learning process. The day will be filled with real-world examples, code snippets, and hands-on labs.
Objectives
Understand, apply, and analyze secure coding best practices related to the OWASP Top 10.
Evaluate and create secure code snippets.
Engage in hands-on labs to reinforce learning.
Detailed Topics and Activities
A.	1. SQL Injection
‚Ä¢	Understanding: Lecture on what SQL Injection is, with real-world examples.
‚Ä¢	Application: Hands-on lab where participants will try to exploit SQL Injection vulnerabilities in a test environment.
‚Ä¢	Hacker's Method: Using basic SQL payloads to manipulate queries.
‚Ä¢	Developer's Strategy: Using parameterized queries to prevent SQL Injection.
‚Ä¢	Analysis: Code review session to identify SQL Injection vulnerabilities.
‚Ä¢	Evaluation: Group discussion to evaluate different mitigation strategies.
‚Ä¢	Creation: Participants will write secure code snippets to prevent SQL Injection.
B.	2. Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
‚Ä¢	Understanding: Explanation of XSS, types of XSS, and its impact.
‚Ä¢	Application: Hands-on lab to exploit and prevent XSS.
‚Ä¢	Hacker's Method: Injecting malicious scripts into web pages.
‚Ä¢	Developer's Strategy: Implementing output encoding and input validation.
‚Ä¢	Analysis: Code review session focusing on potential XSS vulnerabilities.
‚Ä¢	Evaluation: Debate on client-side vs server-side mitigation strategies.
‚Ä¢	Creation: Participants will modify existing code to make it XSS-resistant.
C.	3. Insecure Deserialization
‚Ä¢	Understanding: Introduction to insecure deserialization and its risks.
‚Ä¢	Application: Lab to both exploit and secure deserialization vulnerabilities.
‚Ä¢	Hacker's Method: Manipulating serialized objects for unauthorized access.
‚Ä¢	Developer's Strategy: Implementing secure serialization libraries and methods.
‚Ä¢	Analysis: Review of code snippets that are vulnerable to insecure deserialization.
‚Ä¢	Evaluation: Discussion on the trade-offs between performance and security in serialization.
‚Ä¢	Creation: Writing secure serialization code snippets.
Facilitation Methods
‚Ä¢	Reverse Engineering Session: Participants will reverse-engineer a piece of malware to understand its exploitation strategy.
‚Ä¢	Security Puzzles: Quick puzzles related to secure coding to keep the session interactive.
Real-World Examples and Case Studies
Case Study on SQL Injection: How a major corporation was compromised and the financial implications.
Real-world XSS Attacks: Examples of actual XSS attacks and their impact on businesses.
Guides and Strategies
OWASP Top 10 Cheat Sheet: A quick reference guide for the OWASP Top 10 vulnerabilities and their mitigations.
Secure Coding Handbook: A comprehensive guide on secure coding practices, complete with code snippets and examples.
